==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skylark
<hw>Sky"lark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
lark that mounts and sings as it files, especially the common species
(<spn>Alauda arvensis</spn>) found in Europe and in some parts of Asia,
and celebrated for its melodious song; -- called also <altname>sky
laverock</altname>. See under <er>Lark</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The Australian skylark (<spn>Cincloramphus
cantillans</spn>) is a pipit which has the habit of ascending
perpendicularly like a skylark, but it lacks the song of a true lark.
The Missouri skylark is a pipit (<spn>Anthus Spraguei</spn>) of the
Western United States, resembling the skylark in habit and
song.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skylarking</ent>⟦br⟧
